        </span><span class="comment-date">Jan 16, 2013. 12:52 AM<a id="replytolink_CLW8FWLHBXWRIXS" class="btn btn-mini reply-comment login-required" href="CLW8FWLHBXWRIXS">Reply</a></span></div><div class="txt comment-txt">in this code I have the arduino set up to only read data from A0- all the other pins are in an inactive state.  Then each time I want to get an analog value I call ADCH.  If I'd set the arduino up to only read from a1, I would still call ADCH to get the value.  Read my reply to yasinkeles to get some more info about how I set up the arduino to only read from one input.</div><div id="files" class=""><a name="files"></a></div><div id="commentactioncontainer_CLW8FWLHBXWRIXS" class="comment-actions"><div class="fr mt5"></div></div></div><a name="C6FWYYIHBUZEKJR"></a><div class="comment-entry clearfix toplevel " style="margin-left:0px;"><div class="comment-authorpic"><a href="/member/yasinkeles/"><img src="/static/defaultIMG/user.TINY.gif" alt="" /></a></div><div class="comment-info"><span class="comment-author"><a class="author-link " href="/member/yasinkeles/">yasinkeles</a> says:
