        </span><span class="comment-date">Jan 16, 2013. 12:50 AM<a id="replytolink_CGPCVQ8HBXWRIXN" class="btn btn-mini reply-comment login-required" href="CGPCVQ8HBXWRIXN">Reply</a></span></div><div class="txt comment-txt">yes, but you will get half the sampling rate.  if you want to read from A0 you have to set the last four digits of ADCMUX to zeros: <br> <br>ADCMUX &amp;= B11110000; <br> <br>to read from A1 you set the last four digits to 0001: <br> <br>ADCMUX &amp;= B11110000; <br>ADCMUX |= B00000001; <br> <br>you can read more about this here: <br>http://openenergymonitor.blogspot.com/2012/08/low-level-adc-control-admux.html</div><div id="files" class=""><a name="files"></a></div><div id="commentactioncontainer_CGPCVQ8HBXWRIXN" class="comment-actions"><div class="fr mt5"></div></div></div><a name="CHJGA31HAQ32QSV"></a><div class="comment-entry clearfix toplevel " style="margin-left:0px;"><div class="comment-authorpic"><a href="/member/luis_cordova/"><img src="/static/defaultIMG/user.TINY.gif" alt="" /></a></div><div class="comment-info"><span class="comment-author"><a class="author-link " href="/member/luis_cordova/">luis_cordova</a> says:
